<p class="p">LPS tracks from HiRAM simulations and reanalysis data are extracted using a tracking algorithm that mimics the conventional detection and tracking of LPS by identifying closed isobars (
 <xref rid="r4" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">4</xref>). The LPS activity from HIST simulations are compared with those from ERA-Interim reanalysis as well as from the Sikka archive. See 
 <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.pnas.org/lookup/suppl/doi:10.1073/pnas.1709031115/-/DCSupplemental" xlink:show="new" class="ext-link" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <italic class="italic">SI Appendix</italic>, 
  <italic class="italic">Supporting Methods</italic>
 </ext-link> for details of the LPS tracking algorithm. The storm intensity is measured by the maximum pressure depth (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i24" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) achieved by the storm during its life cycle. 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i25" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is defined as the difference between the value of outermost closed isobar and the central minimum pressure of the storm. It is also to be noted that here we only consider storms that lasted 3 d or more. The LPS activity is quantitatively represented by an SAI which is track density-weighted by wind speed (
 <xref rid="r17" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">17</xref>) as
 <disp-formula id="uneq4" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="me4" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">S</mi>
      <mi class="mi">A</mi>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">I</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mi class="mi">y</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <munderover class="munderover">
       <mo largeop="true" movablelimits="false" symmetric="true" class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mo class="mo">−</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        </mrow>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mo class="mo">+</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
         <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        </mrow>
       </mrow>
      </munderover>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <munderover class="munderover">
        <mo largeop="true" movablelimits="false" symmetric="true" class="mo">∑</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">y</mi>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
          <mi class="mi">y</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">y</mi>
         <mo class="mo">+</mo>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
          <mi class="mi">y</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
       </munderover>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">U</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">c</mi>
         <mi class="mi">a</mi>
         <mi class="mi">t</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">y</italic> are the longitude and latitude of the center of LPS, 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i26" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">x</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> = 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i27" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">y</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> = 1.5°, and 
 <italic class="italic">U</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">cat</italic>
 </sub> is the wind speed magnitude based on the intensity category of the LPS. The values of 
 <italic class="italic">U</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">cat</italic>
 </sub> are 4.25, 11, 15, 20, and 27.5, respectively, for LPS categories of Low (1 hPa 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i30" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i31" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i32" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> 2 hPa), Depression (2 hPa 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i33" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i34" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i35" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> 4 hPa), Deep Depression (4 hPa 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i36" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i37" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i38" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> 10 hPa), Cyclonic Storm (10 hPa 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i39" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i40" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i41" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> 16 hPa), and Severe Cyclonic Storm (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i42" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <mi class="mi">L</mi>
    <mi class="mi">P</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i43" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">&gt;</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> 16 hPa).
</p>
